sub_title: Double Honours M.A. in Philosophy and Art History
summary:
Recent graduate from the University of Rijeka with a double major MA in Philosophy and Art History. Currently pursuing opportunities in academia and the arts. Open to jobs in a wide area of artistic fields, as well as those relating to humanities in general.

My main passion is philosophy, specifically its branches of aesthetics and ethics. In my years of studying the discipline, I maintained a good academic record, and became very fond of these fields of study. I aspire to deepen my knowledge and experiences in both the theoretical research of philosophical topics, and its application in an academic environment.

Working in a museum as an apprentice museum educator, I've also grown fond of any work that connects art pieces to a wider audience. I am very passionate about art, having studied both its history and its practice. I grew up in an artistic environment, and was always encouraged to express myself creatively. This led me to my degree in graphic design from a vocational school of applied arts, as well as a university major in art history later on. I thrive in a creative environment, and would love to be surrounded by art in my day-to-day life.
